Investigate the `calllog` call-logging pattern used by this project's CLI
commands (package `internal/calllog`, type `Tracker` with `calllog.Start`,
`Tracker.RecordOutput`, `Tracker.SetOutputBytes`, `Tracker.SetOutputTokens`,
`Tracker.Finish`, and the package-level helper `calllog.Track`).

Produce a short technical summary:

1) List every non-test `.go` file under `internal/cc/` and `internal/common/`
   that calls `calllog.Start(...)`, with file paths.
2) For each of those files, say which method it uses to hand output to the
   tracker before calling `Finish`: `RecordOutput(...)`, `SetOutputBytes(...)`,
   or `SetOutputTokens(...)` — and how many call sites of that kind appear in
   the file.
3) State whether the package-level convenience helper `calllog.Track(...)`
   (an alternative to calling `Start`/`Finish` by hand) is actually used by
   any command file, anywhere in the repository.

Answer compactly, as a structured list. Do not modify any files — this is an
investigation and summary task only.
